the CMakeList.txt
has the main configuration for building the code. 
You can keep adding other targets or what not by editing and extending this file. 
The main program are optical_flow and optical_flow_frames which use Brox. If you want to copy this to a different directory make sure you copy the other Brox executable as well. The computer needs to have tbb module loaded (libtbb) in order for the GPU to work. 

For the program to work with activity recognition copy the optical_flow_frames and Brox executables to the examples/LRCN_activity_recognition



CUDA_FLOW
***************************************************************************************************************************
***************************************************************************************************************************

This code shows several examples for using the dense optical flow methods from the GPU module of the OpenCV Library.
The version of the OpenCV library should be equal or higher than 2.4.
You should have a NVIDA graphic card and the OpenCV library compiled with CUDA support to run the examples.

***************************************************************************************************************************
***************************************************************************************************************************

Compiling the program
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
In the program folder please type:
mkdir release
cd release
cmake ..
make

After compiling and linking you should have executables such as:
brox_flox
farneback_flow
lk_flow (this method seems to have some bugs in OpenCV 2.4.3)

***************************************************************************************************************************
***************************************************************************************************************************

Running the program
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The program accepts command line arguments.
To run each of the methods you should pass the path of a video file.
Examples:

./brox_flow video.avi
./farneback_flow video.avi
./lk_flow video.avi

***************************************************************************************************************************
***************************************************************************************************************************

